Note: Runa Terraform Infrastructure as Code Module
Note: Provides comprehensive Terraform integration for infrastructure management
Note: Following Runa specification patterns with natural language syntax

Note: Built-in functions are automatically available in Runa programs
Note: No imports required for built-ins like create_runtime_error, execute_command, etc.

Note: Terraform Configuration type definition
Type TerraformConfig is Dictionary with:
    terraform_version as String,
    working_directory as String,
    backend_config as Dictionary[String, Any],
    providers as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    variables as Dictionary[String, Any],
    outputs as Dictionary[String, Any],
    modules as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    resources as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    data_sources as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    locals as Dictionary[String, Any],
    configuration_files as List[String],
    state_file_location as String,
    lock_file_location as String

Note: Terraform State type definition
Type TerraformState is Dictionary with:
    version as Integer,
    serial as Integer,
    lineage as String,
    backend as Dictionary[String, Any],
    modules as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    resources as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    outputs as Dictionary[String, Any],
    terraform_version as String,
    check_results as Optional[List[Dictionary[String, Any]]],
    timestamp as Integer

Note: Terraform Plan type definition
Type TerraformPlan is Dictionary with:
    plan_id as String,
    terraform_version as String,
    format_version as String,
    variables as Dictionary[String, Any],
    planned_values as Dictionary[String, Any],
    resource_changes as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    configuration as Dictionary[String, Any],
    prior_state as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    relevant_attributes as List[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    output_changes as Dictionary[String, Any],
    timestamp as Integer,
    errored as Boolean

Note: Terraform Resource Change type definition
Type TerraformResourceChange is Dictionary with:
    address as String,
    mode as String,
    resource_type as String,
    name as String,
    provider_name as String,
    change as Dictionary[String, Any],
    action_reason as Optional[String],
    before as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    after as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]],
    before_sensitive as Optional[List[String]],
    after_sensitive as Optional[List[String]],
    after_unknown as Optional[List[String]]

Note: Terraform Module type definition
Type TerraformModule is Dictionary with:
    name as String,
    source as String,
    version as Optional[String],
    input_variables as Dictionary[String, Any],
    output_values as Dictionary[String, Any],
    resources as List[String],
    child_modules as List[String],
    depends_on as List[String],
    providers as Dictionary[String, String],
    count as Optional[Integer],
    for_each as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]

Note: Terraform Provider type definition
Type TerraformProvider is Dictionary with:
    name as String,
    alias as Optional[String],
    version as Optional[String],
    configuration as Dictionary[String, Any],
    required_version as Optional[String],
    source as Optional[String]

Note: Execute Terraform command with error handling
Process called "execute_terraform_command" that takes command as String and parameters as List[String] and working_directory as Optional[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let full_command be "terraform " with message command
        For each param in parameters:
            Set full_command to full_command with message " " with message param
        
        Note: Change to working directory if specified
        If working_directory is not null:
            Set full_command to "cd " with message working_directory with message " && " with message full_command
        
        Let result be execute_command with command as full_command
        
        If result["exit_code"] is not equal to 0:
            Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_command" and context as dictionary with:
                "command" as command,
                "parameters" as parameters,
                "working_directory" as working_directory,
                "exit_code" as result["exit_code"],
                "error_output" as result["stderr"]
        
        Return dictionary with:
            "success" as true,
            "output" as result["stdout"],
            "command" as command,
            "working_directory" as working_directory
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary with:
            "success" as false,
            "error" as error["message"],
            "command" as command,
            "working_directory" as working_directory

Note: Initialize Terraform configuration
Process called "terraform_init" that takes working_directory as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    
    Note: Add backend configuration
    If options contains key "backend_config":
        For each key and value in options["backend_config"]:
            Add "-backend-config=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Note: Add upgrade option
    If options contains key "upgrade" and options["upgrade"]:
        Add "-upgrade" to parameters
    
    Note: Add reconfigure option
    If options contains key "reconfigure" and options["reconfigure"]:
        Add "-reconfigure" to parameters
    
    Note: Add migrate state option
    If options contains key "migrate_state" and options["migrate_state"]:
        Add "-migrate-state" to parameters
    
    Note: Add plugin directory
    If options contains key "plugin_dir":
        Add "-plugin-dir=" with message options["plugin_dir"] to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "init" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_init" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return true

Note: Validate Terraform configuration
Process called "terraform_validate" that takes working_directory as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "-json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "validate" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_validate" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Let validation_result be parse_json with json_string as result["output"]
    Return dictionary with:
        "valid" as validation_result["valid"],
        "error_count" as validation_result["error_count"],
        "warning_count" as validation_result["warning_count"],
        "diagnostics" as validation_result["diagnostics"],
        "working_directory" as working_directory

Note: Create Terraform plan
Process called "terraform_plan" that takes working_directory as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns TerraformPlan:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "-json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add variable file
    If options contains key "var_file":
        Add "-var-file=" with message options["var_file"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add individual variables
    If options contains key "vars":
        For each key and value in options["vars"]:
            Add "-var=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Note: Add target resources
    If options contains key "targets":
        For each target in options["targets"]:
            Add "-target=" with message target to parameters
    
    Note: Add destroy flag
    If options contains key "destroy" and options["destroy"]:
        Add "-destroy" to parameters
    
    Note: Add output file
    Let plan_file be working_directory with message "/terraform.tfplan"
    If options contains key "out":
        Set plan_file to options["out"]
    Add "-out=" with message plan_file to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "plan" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_plan" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Note: Parse plan output and show detailed plan
    Let show_params be list containing
    Add "-json" to show_params
    Add plan_file to show_params
    
    Let show_result be execute_terraform_command with command as "show" and parameters as show_params and working_directory as working_directory
    If not show_result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_plan" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as "Failed to show plan details"
    
    Let plan_data be parse_json with json_string as show_result["output"]
    Return parse_terraform_plan with plan_data as plan_data

Note: Apply Terraform configuration
Process called "terraform_apply" that takes working_directory as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    
    Note: Add auto-approve if specified
    If options contains key "auto_approve" and options["auto_approve"]:
        Add "-auto-approve" to parameters
    
    Note: Apply from plan file
    If options contains key "plan_file":
        Add options["plan_file"] to parameters
    Else:
        Note: Add variable file
        If options contains key "var_file":
            Add "-var-file=" with message options["var_file"] to parameters
        
        Note: Add individual variables
        If options contains key "vars":
            For each key and value in options["vars"]:
                Add "-var=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
        
        Note: Add target resources
        If options contains key "targets":
            For each target in options["targets"]:
                Add "-target=" with message target to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "apply" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_apply" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Note: Get outputs after apply
    Let outputs be terraform_output with working_directory as working_directory
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "success" as true,
        "working_directory" as working_directory,
        "outputs" as outputs,
        "apply_output" as result["output"]

Note: Destroy Terraform-managed infrastructure
Process called "terraform_destroy" that takes working_directory as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    
    Note: Add auto-approve if specified
    If options contains key "auto_approve" and options["auto_approve"]:
        Add "-auto-approve" to parameters
    
    Note: Add variable file
    If options contains key "var_file":
        Add "-var-file=" with message options["var_file"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add individual variables
    If options contains key "vars":
        For each key and value in options["vars"]:
            Add "-var=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Note: Add target resources
    If options contains key "targets":
        For each target in options["targets"]:
            Add "-target=" with message target to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "destroy" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_destroy" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "success" as true,
        "working_directory" as working_directory,
        "destroy_output" as result["output"]

Note: Get Terraform outputs
Process called "terraform_output" that takes working_directory as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "-json" to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "output" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Note: Return empty outputs if command fails (might be no outputs)
        Return dictionary containing
    
    Return parse_json with json_string as result["output"]

Note: Get specific Terraform output
Process called "terraform_output_value" that takes working_directory as String and output_name as String returns String:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "-raw" to parameters
    Add output_name to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "output" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_output_value" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "output_name" as output_name,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return trim with text as result["output"]

Note: Show Terraform state
Process called "terraform_show" that takes working_directory as String and state_file as Optional[String] returns TerraformState:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add "-json" to parameters
    
    Note: Add state file if specified
    If state_file is not null:
        Add state_file to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "show" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_show" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "state_file" as state_file,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Let state_data be parse_json with json_string as result["output"]
    Return parse_terraform_state with state_data as state_data

Note: List Terraform resources
Process called "terraform_state_list" that takes working_directory as String and address_filter as Optional[String] returns List[String]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    
    Note: Add address filter
    If address_filter is not null:
        Add address_filter to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "state list" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_state_list" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "address_filter" as address_filter,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Let resources_list be list containing
    Let lines be split with text as result["output"] and delimiter as "\n"
    For each line in lines:
        Let trimmed_line be trim with text as line
        If not (is_empty with collection as trimmed_line):
            Add trimmed_line to resources_list
    
    Return resources_list

Note: Show specific Terraform resource
Process called "terraform_state_show" that takes working_directory as String and resource_address as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add resource_address to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "state show" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_state_show" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "resource_address" as resource_address,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "resource_address" as resource_address,
        "resource_details" as result["output"],
        "working_directory" as working_directory

Note: Import existing resource into Terraform state
Process called "terraform_import" that takes working_directory as String and resource_address as String and resource_id as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    Add resource_address to parameters
    Add resource_id to parameters
    
    Note: Add variable file
    If options contains key "var_file":
        Add "-var-file=" with message options["var_file"] to parameters
    
    Note: Add individual variables
    If options contains key "vars":
        For each key and value in options["vars"]:
            Add "-var=" with message key with message "=" with message value to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "import" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_import" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "resource_address" as resource_address,
            "resource_id" as resource_id,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return true

Note: Remove resource from Terraform state
Process called "terraform_state_rm" that takes working_directory as String and resource_addresses as List[String] returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
    
    Note: Add all resource addresses
    For each address in resource_addresses:
        Add address to parameters
    
    Let result be execute_terraform_command with command as "state rm" and parameters as parameters and working_directory as working_directory
    If not result["success"]:
        Throw create_runtime_error with operation as "terraform_state_rm" and context as dictionary with:
            "working_directory" as working_directory,
            "resource_addresses" as resource_addresses,
            "error" as result["error"]
    
    Return true

Note: Move resource in Terraform state
Process called "terraform_state_mv" that takes working_directory as String and source_address as String and destination_address as String returns Boolean:
    Let parameters be list containing
